description.narrative: (Philippines): Advancing Philippine Competitiveness (COMPETE) assists the Philippines to improve its competitiveness through better infrastructure, advancement of key industries and better access to credit. FY 2016 funds will support Philippine government Public-Private Partnership priority infrastructure projects, provide technical assistance to expand logistics and transport systems, raise power supply, and lower electricity costs. FY 2016 funds will continue assistance to develop and procure the Bohol Bulk Water and Sanitation Project, and provide support to the planning and prioritization of tourism water projects that will provide Level 3 water system to 30 waterless municipalities in Palawan. COMPETE will develop a successor national tourism strategy, food industry roadmaps, and agribusiness value chains (e.g. seaweed and cacao). Resources will also help businesses gain access to credit through business development services and an information campaign for the credit information system..
